cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use nae, please cite it as below."
title: "nae: Build-Time Dataflow Validation for LLM Pipeline Graphs"
abstract: >-
  A thin declarative layer over LangGraph that compiles a >-wired agent pipeline
  to a native LangGraph StateGraph and, before compiling, runs a forward may/must
  dataflow analysis over the graph. It fails the build with zero model calls when
  a node reads a state key nothing produces, a branch is unwired, or parallel
  branches write an unreduced key.
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/TeeratP/nae"
url: "https://github.com/TeeratP/nae"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - agent frameworks
  - LangGraph
  - dataflow analysis
  - static analysis
  - NLP pipelines
